    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Patri et Filii et Spiritus Sancti. Anno Deo propitio pontificatus
                        domini nostri <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/2410">Benedicti</persName>
                        summi <rs key="#Popes">pontifici</rs> et universali papae in apostolica
                        sacratissima beati Petri hapostoli Domini sede anno tertio atque imperante
                        domino piissimo perpetuo haugustus <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/239">Ottone</persName> ha Deo coronato pacifico magno <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperatore</rs> in Italia vero anno sextodecimo, die
                        septimo mensis ... indictione undecima, <placeName ref="#places/594"
                            >Ravennae</placeName>. Etenim quae gesta esse videntur prolixis
                        temporibus memoriter retineri non possumus, ideo scripture vinculis anotari
                        ... cum Christi auxilium dum adessem ego quidem <persName
                            key="#Tabellio #Consul/hypatos" ref="#people/1555">Iohannis</persName>
                        Dei nutu ex genere <rs key="#Consul/hypatos">consulis</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Tabellio">tabellio</rs> huius civitatis Ravennae, in <rs
                            key="#Curtes">curte</rs> ...fivit... ibique mecum pariter bonissimis
                        atque <rs key="#Vir_inluster">illustrissimis viris</rs> et bonae hobinionis
                        atque laudabilis famae viris corum nomina haec sunt, idest: <persName
                            key="#Vir_inluster"><name ref="Petrus de Traversaria">Petrus qui vocatur
                                de Traversaria</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke #Vir_inluster"><name ref="Paulus de Traversaria"
                                >Paulus <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux</rs> de
                            Traversaria</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Vir_inluster #Consul/hypatos" ref="#people/92"><name
                                ref="Iohannes">Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Consul/hypatos">consul(e)</rs> et pater civitatis, <persName
                            key="#Vir_inluster"><name ref="Paulus">Paulus</name></persName> qui
                        vocatur ... <persName><name ref="Egilo">Egila</name></persName>,
                                <persName><name ref="Rodualdus">Rodaldus</name></persName> filio
                                <persName><name ref="Rodualdus">Rodaldus</name></persName> magister
                        militum, <persName key="#Consul/hypatos"><name
                                ref="Leo/Liutio de Anestaliolo">Leo</name>
                            <rs key="#Consul/hypatos">consule</rs> qui vocatur Liutio de
                            Anestaliolo</persName>, <persName><name ref="Paulus de Gandilo"
                                >Paulus</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Andreas de Gandilo">Andreas</name></persName> germani de
                        Gandilo, <persName><name ref="Petrus de Antio">Petrus de
                            Antio</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Atto"
                            >Atio</name></persName> filio suo, <persName><name ref="Richardus"
                                >Richardo</name></persName> fil(io) quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Benotus">Benotus</name></persName>, <persName><name
                                ref="Martinus de Magno">Martinus de Magno</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#vassusOf"><name ref="Everardus"
                            >Verardo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Consul/hypatos"><name
                                ref="Romanus">Romanus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Consul/hypatos">consul(e)</rs> et <persName><name ref="Paulus"
                                >Paulo</name></persName> filio suo, <persName key="#Chancellor"
                                ><name ref="Bernardus">Bernardo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellario</rs> et aliis plures qui longum est
                        atscribendum; in nostri et homnium presentiam haccedens dominus predictus
                        Everardus <rs key="#vassusOf">vassus</rs>
                        <rs key="#dominus/seniorOf">dominus</rs>
                        <persName key="#Marquis/duke #Palatine_count #dominus/seniorOf"
                            >Anselmus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchio</rs> et <rs key="#Palatine_count">comes
                            palatii</rs> domni Ottonis imperatoris, pariter cum Bernardo
                        cancellarius( j) et adpreenderunt cantum muri de mansione(k) pedeplana in
                        interius ... ac civitate(l) Ravennae, in regione ... et misit in manum
                        domini Romanus(m) cons(ulis) qui vocatur Romizo et in manum Bonizo filio
                        Petronio seo et Petro et Petronia(n) germana(o) et Romanus consul qui
                        vocatur(p) Romizo declaravit et dixerunt: ‘Ecce investimus vobis de omnes
                        pertinetias in integrum de ista mansione qui fuit de quondam Paulus qui
                        vocabatur de Romano(q) et ge... pertinentias vestras de locum qui vocatur
                        Manova, situs(r) territorio Corneliense, plebe Sancti Petri in Brusio(s),
                        salva querela; unde reclamastis per tres vicibus in placitis domini Anselmi
                        marchionis et comitis palatio domini Ottonis imperatoris'. Et ipse Romanus
                        consul(e) qui vocatur Romizo pariter cum Bonizo nepoti suo seo et a Petro et
                        a Petronia germana sicut dixerunt: '...nos eam sic recepimus et deprecamur
                        vos homnes pro futurum testimonium'. Hoc si … hec … dan … um et diem et
                        mense et indictione ut s(upra) undecima, Ravenna...</ab>
